Description: Sherd of pottery closed vessel body; coarse brown ware with red surface; incised decoration outside. Red-brown Nile silt fabric with yellow slip.
Curator's comments: Unidentified type, on the basis of the fabric and firing technology used, this is most likely Ptolemaic.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IC.138)
